Description
-----------
This assignment implements the `minls` and `minget` utilities for reading
MINIX Version 3 filesystem images. Both programs share common filesystem
code in `minix_fs.c` and use the interfaces defined in `minix_fs.h`.

`minls` lists the contents of a directory inside a MINIX filesystem
image, similar to `ls -l`.  
`minget` copies a file out of a MINIX filesystem image and writes it
either to stdout or to a specified output file.

Files
-----
Makefile
    Builds `minls` and `minget` using the flags:
    `-Wall -ansi -pedantic -g`.

minix_fs.h
    Header file shared by both programs. Defines structures, constants,
    and function prototypes for the filesystem reader.

minix_fs.c
    Shared filesystem code. Handles:
        - Option parsing
        - Reading the partition table
        - Detecting and validating MINIX partitions
        - Superblock parsing
        - Inode lookup and path traversal
        - Directory listing helper functions
        - File reading, including holes, indirect blocks, and
          double-indirect blocks
    This file is used by both `minls` and `minget`.

minls.c
    Implementation of the `minls` utility:
        - Parses arguments
        - Canonicalizes paths
        - Looks up the target inode
        - Prints directory contents or file metadata

minget.c
    Implementation of the `minget` utility:
        - Parses arguments
        - Finds the target file
        - Copies file contents to stdout or a destination file

How to Build
------------
Run:

    make

This produces:
    ./minls
    ./minget

To clean object files:

    make clean

How to Run
----------
List root directory of an unpartitioned image:

    ./minls TestImage

List a path inside the filesystem:

    ./minls TestImage /src

List with verbose information:

    ./minls -v TestImage

Work inside a primary partition:

    ./minls -p 0 HardDisk

Work inside a subpartition:

    ./minls -p 0 -s 2 HardDisk /home/pnico/Message

Extract a file:

    ./minget TestImage /Hello > out.txt

Extract to stdout:

    ./minget TestImage /Hello /dev/stdout

